                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d549">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">550.S1/1155: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Chairman of the American Delegation</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Hull</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1933-07-17T21:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 17, 1933—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>152. Your 133, July 14. Norman Davis has raised the point that, inasmuch as the
                    Disarmament Conference<note n="76" xml:id="d549fn76">For correspondence
                        concerning the Conference for the Reduction and Limitation of Armaments, see
                            <ref target="#pg_1">pp. 1</ref> ff.</note> is scheduled to meet on
                    October 16, it would be unfortunate to have the Economic Conference reconvene
                    about October 1, since this would necessitate both international conferences
                    being held simultaneously. While the President is not inclined to take any
                    position in this matter, he desires me to call it to your attention.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
